40|$|A mirror {{reflection}} on metallic grids and the diffusion scattering on rough surfaces at the resonance excitation of surface <b>electromagnetic</b> <b>modes</b> are investigated {{in the paper}} aiming at the analytical theory construction of the reflection and absorption of bounded {{in space and time}} optical signals from non-smooth metallic surfaces under conditions of the resonance excitation of surface <b>electromagnetic</b> <b>modes.</b> The spectral decomposition method for the finding of the connection between amplitudes of falling and reflected signals at the resonance excitation of surface <b>electromagnetic</b> <b>modes</b> has been formulated. As a result the analytical theory for the description of the reflection and absorption of a bounded in space and time ligth signal at the falling on a metallic grid without coating, with dielectric coating and on a rough metallic surface has been developed as well as the new method for the calculation of the connection between falling and reflected amplitudes of a bounded light pulse at the falling on a metallic surface. Some new effects have been forecasted. The paper results may find their field of application in laser technology, diffraction optics, surface photophysicsAvailable from VNTIC / VNTIC - Scientific & Technical Information Centre of RussiaSIGLERURussian Federatio...|$|R
